Class AbstractJiraRemoteLinkBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.testah.framework.report.jira.AbstractJiraRemoteLinkBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JiraRemoteLinkBuilder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicJiraRemoteLinkBuilder

    public abstract class AbstractJiraRemoteLinkBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements JiraRemoteLinkBuilder
    The Interface JiraRemoteLinkBuilder. This class is a helper to do some of the common task with implementing JiraRemoteLinkBuilder.

      • getBaseRemoteIssueLinkDto

        protected RemoteIssueLinkDto getBaseRemoteIssueLinkDto(java.lang.String relationship,
                                                       java.lang.String linkType,
                                                       java.lang.String name,
                                                       java.lang.String summary,
                                                       java.lang.String title,
                                                       java.lang.String url,
                                                       java.lang.String iconTitle,
                                                       java.lang.String icon2Title,
                                                       java.lang.String icon2Url,
                                                       java.lang.String source)
        Gets base remote issue link dto models jira api remote link object is what is passed to jira api.
        Parameters:
        relationship - the relationship is the type of remote link and its relationship with the jira ticket
        linkType - the link type (see jira doc)
        name - the name is the name of the remote issue link
        summary - the summary is the remote link summary can be desc or more with status information
        title - the title
        url - the url
        iconTitle - the icon title for the remote link icon
        icon2Title - the icon 2 title for the status icon
        icon2Url - the icon 2 url for the status icon
        source - the source is the classpath to the testplan
        Returns:
        the base remote issue link dto

      • validateUrl

        protected java.lang.String validateUrl(java.lang.String link,
                                       java.lang.String errorTip)
        Validate url string. Checks that the string is not empty, if it is will put in a placeholder. Also ensures it starts with http Jira requires a valid link, and will fail if it is not.
        Parameters:
        link - the link must be a valid link starting with http
        errorTip - the error tip is added as a query parma to the fake link to help know what why fake link is used.
        Returns:
        the string the link or a value that is not empty using a fake link
